div.p:
For my selfe also, me thinkes it will better beseeme my yeares to heale, then to teach my Ancients; to enkindle their affections, then to enforme their iudgements. And whereas Paul bids Titus preach zeale with all authority, though in mine owne name I craue your patience, and audience, yet
in his name that is the first of the creatures, and Amen, I counsell him that hath an eare, to heare what the Spirit saith to the Churches;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 Be zealous.
